'''Roshon Felix Romar Jordan van Eijma''' (born 9 June 1998) is a [[Curaçao]]an professional [[association football|footballer]] who plays as a [[centre-back]] for {{Dutch football updater|RKCWaalwi}} club [[RKC Waalwijk]]. Born in the Netherlands, he plays for the [[Curaçao national football team|Curaçao national team]].

==Club career==
===Roda JC Kerkrade===
He made his [[Eerste Divisie]] debut for [[Roda JC Kerkrade]] on 28 September 2018 in a game against [[SC Cambuur]].<ref>{{cite web|publisher=Worldfootball|url=https://www.worldfootball.net/match-report/ma8743060/lineup/|title=Game Report by Worldfootball|date=28 September 2018}}</ref>

===Preußen Münster===
In September 2020, he moved from Kerkrade to [[SC Preußen Münster|Preußen Münster]].<ref>{{cite news |title=Van Eijma: Preußen ist ein cooler Klub |url=https://www.kicker.de/van-eijma-preussen-ist-ein-cooler-klub-784007/artikel |work=kicker |date=7 September 2020 |language=de-DE}}</ref> He played his first game on 13 December against [[Rot-Weiß Oberhausen]], in which he was sent off with a red card in the 54th minute.<ref>{{cite news |title=Tragischer Held Roshon van Eijma – Preußen verlieren 0:2 bei RW Oberhausen |url=https://www.muensterschezeitung.de/sport/preussen-muenster/tragischer-held-roshon-van-eijma-preussen-verlieren-02-bei-rw-oberhausen-778819 |work=Münster Zeitung |date=13 December 2020 |language=de}}</ref> In his first season in Germany, Van Eijma played eleven games in the [[Regionalliga West]] and won the [[Westphalian Cup]] with the club.<ref>{{cite news |title=Krombacher Westfalenpokal: Preußen Münster holt den Pott |url=https://www.flvw.de/news/detail/krombacher-westfalenpokal-preussen-muenster-holt-den-pott/ |work=FLVW |date=29 May 2021 |language=de}}</ref>

On 17 August 2021, his contract was terminated by mutual agreement. Upon his release, sporting director for Preußen Münster, [[Peter Niemeyer]] stated: "As nice as it is to have a national player in your own ranks, so great are the difficulties associated with it. For a [[Regionalliga]] team that does not plan for international breaks in its schedule, the many national team selections were unfortunately no longer feasible in the end. This was not a satisfactory situation for neither player nor club. We thank Roshon for his commitment and wish him all the best for the future."<ref>{{cite web |last1=Weskamp |first1=Marcel |title=Vertrag mit Roshon van Eijma aufgelöst |url=https://scpreussen-muenster.de/news/vertrag-mit-roshon-van-eijma-aufgeloest/ |website=SC Preußen Münster |language=de-DE |date=17 August 2021}}</ref>

===TOP Oss===
Ten days after being released by Preußen Münster, Van Eijma signed with Eerste Divisie club [[TOP Oss]].<ref>{{cite web |title=Roshon van Eijma naar TOP Oss |url=https://toposs.nl/roshon-van-eijma-naar-top-oss/ |website=TOP Oss |language=nl |date=26 August 2021}}</ref> On 9 October, he made his debut as a second-half substitute for [[Nicolas Abdat]] in the 2–1 loss to [[FC Eindhoven]] away at [[Jan Louwers Stadion]].<ref>{{cite web |title=Eindhoven vs. TOP Oss – 9 October 2021 |url=https://int.soccerway.com/matches/2021/10/09/netherlands/eerste-divisie/fc-eindhoven/bvo-top-oss/3512868/ |website=Soccerway |access-date=15 October 2021}}</ref>

===RKC Waalwijk===
On 2 July 2024, van Eijma signed a two-year contract with [[RKC Waalwijk]].<ref>{{cite web|publisher=RKC Waalwijk|url=https://www.rkcwaalwijk.nl/verdediging-van-rkc-waalwijk-krijgt-meer-vorm-met-komst-roshon-van-eijma|title=Verdediging van RKC Waalwijk krijgt meer vorm met komst Roshon van Eijma|trans-title=RKC Waalwijk's defense takes shape with the arrival of Roshon van Eijma|date=2 July 2024|access-date=15 July 2024|language=nl}}</ref>

==International career==
Van Eijma debuted for the [[Curaçao national football team|Curaçao national team]] in a 5–0 [[2022 FIFA World Cup qualification]] win over [[Saint Vincent and the Grenadines national football team|Saint Vincent and the Grenadines]] on 25 March 2021.<ref name="Global Sports Archive 2021">{{cite web | title=Match Report of Curaçao vs St. Vincent and the Grenadines – 2021-03-25 – WC Qualification | website=Global Sports Archive | date=25 March 2021 | url=https://globalsportsarchive.com/match/soccer/2021-03-25/curacao-vs-st-vincent-and-the-grenadines/2151404/ | access-date=26 March 2021}}</ref>

